SDEV-M01 Understand: Practice & Review Algorithms
Problem solving can be fun; here are some problem solving games for you to attempt practicing how to solve algorithms.

YellowOut is a game where your yellow car is stuck in a parking lot. The objective is for you to move the cars, trucks and automobiles to get your car out of the parking lot. Cars, trucks and automobiles including your yellow car can only move forward and backward.
http://www.quickflashgames.com/games/yellow_out/

Crazy Cube is a game where your goal is to link every pair of like colored markers to complete a cube. You cannot link cells diagonally and all black cells are blocked.
http://www.abelmartin.com/rj/crazy_cube.html

Shape Patterns is a game where your monster truck is trying to get across the bridge. You must complete the puzzle by correctly placing the missing shapes in the pattern.  
http://www.abcya.com/shape_patterns.htm

Sudoku is a number placement puzzle where the objective is to fill 9x9 grid with digits so that each column, each row, and each of the nine 3x3 grids contains all of the digits from 1 to 9.
http://www.websudoku.com/